The paper proposes a method for interpreting and visualizing deep neural network predictions, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves segmenting the input image at multiple scales, which is also a common technique in computer vision. The paper also mentions the use of a model-agnostic prediction difference method, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or natural language processing (cs.CL) depending on the specific application. Finally, the paper discusses the visual quality of the generated saliency maps, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
